quran[564]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,Of what do they question one another
  78,2,Of the mighty tiding
  78,3,whereon they are at variance
  78,4,No indeed; they shall soon know
  78,5,"Again, no indeed; they shall soon know"
  78,6,Have We not made the earth as a cradle
  78,7,and the mountains as pegs
  78,8,And We created you in pairs
  78,9,and We appointed your sleep for a rest
  78,10,and We appointed night for a garment
  78,11,and We appointed day for a livelihood
  78,12,And We have built above you seven strong ones
  78,13,and We appointed a blazing lamp
  78,14,and have sent down out of the rainclouds water cascading
  78,15,that We may bring forth thereby grain and plants
  78,16,and gardens luxuriant
  78,17,Surely the Day of Decision is an appointed time
  78,18,"the day the Trumpet is blown, and you shall come in troops"
  78,19,"and heaven is opened, and become gates"
  78,20,"and the mountains are set in motion, and become a vapour"
  78,21,"Behold, Gehenna has become an ambush"
  78,22,for the insolent a resort
  78,23,therein to tarry for ages
  78,24,tasting therein neither coolness nor any drink
  78,25,save boiling water and pus
  78,26,for a suitable recompense
  78,27,They indeed hoped not for a reckoning
  78,28,and they cried loud lies to Our signs
  78,29,and everything We have numbered in a Book
  78,30,Taste! We shall increase you not save in chastisement
  78,31,Surely for the godfearing awaits a place of security
  78,32,gardens and vineyards
  78,33,"and maidens with swelling breasts, like of age"
  78,34,and a cup overflowing
  78,35,"Therein they shall hear no idle talk, no cry of lies"
  78,36,"for a recompense from thy Lord, a gift, a reckoning"
  78,37,"Lord of the heavens and earth, and all that between them is, the All-merciful of whom they have no power to speak"
  78,38,"Upon the day when the Spirit and the angels stand in ranks they shall speak not, save him to whom the All-merciful has given leave, and who speaks aright"
  78,39,That is the true day; so whosoever wills takes unto his Lord a resort
  78,40,"Lo, We have warned you of a nigh chastisement, upon the day when a man shall behold what his hands have forwarded, and the unbeliever shall say, 'O would that I were dust"
  79,1,By those that pluck out vehemently
  79,2,and those that draw out violently
  79,3,by those that swim serenely
  79,4,and those that outstrip suddenly
  79,5,by those that direct an affair
  79,6,Upon the day when the first blast shivers
  79,7,and the second blast follows it
  79,8,hearts upon that day shall be athrob
  79,9,and their eyes shall be humbled
  79,10,"They shall say, 'What, are we being restored as we were before"
  79,11,"What, when we are bones old and wasted"
  79,12,"They shall say, 'That then were a losing return"
  79,13,But it shall be only a single scare
  79,14,"and behold, they are awakened"
  79,15,Hast thou received the story of Moses
  79,16,"When his Lord called to him in the holy valley, Towa"
  79,17,Go to Pharaoh; he has waxed insolent
  79,18,"And say, \"Hast thou the will to purify thyself"
  79,19,"and that I should guide thee to thy Lord, then thou shalt fear"
  79,20,So he showed him the great sign
  79,21,"but he cried lies, and rebelled"
  79,22,then he turned away hastily
  79,23,then he mustered
  79,24,"and proclaimed, and he said, 'I am your Lord, the Most High"
  79,25,So God seized him with the chastisement of the Last World and the First
  79,26,Surely in that is a lesson for him who fears
  79,27,"What, are you stronger in constitution or the heaven He built"
  79,28,"He lifted up its vault, and levelled it"
  79,29,"and darkened its night, and brought forth its forenoon"
  79,30,and the earth-after that He spread it out
  79,31,therefrom brought forth its waters and its pastures
  79,32,and the mountains He set firm
  79,33,an enjoyment for you and your flocks
  79,34,"Then, when the Great Catastrophe comes"
  79,35,upon the day when man shall remember what he has striven
  79,36,and Hell is advanced for whoever sees
  79,37,then as for him who was insolent
  79,38,and preferred the present life
  79,39,surely Hell shall be the refuge
  79,40,But as for him who feared the Station of his Lord and forbade the soul its caprice
  79,41,surely Paradise shall be the refuge
  79,42,"They will question thee concerning the Hour, when it shall berth"
  79,43,"What art thou about, to mention it"
  79,44,Unto thy Lord is the final end of it
  79,45,Thou art only the warner of him who fears it
  79,46,"It shall be as if; on the day they see it, they have but tarried for an evening, or its forenoon"
  80,1,He frowned and turned away
  80,2,that the blind man came to him
  80,3,And what should teach thee? Perchance he would cleanse him
  80,4,"or yet remember, and the Reminder profit him"
  80,5,But the self-sufficient
  80,6,to him thou attendest
  80,7,"though it is not thy concern, if he does not cleanse himself"
  80,8,And he who comes to thee eagerly
  80,9,and fearfully
  80,10,to him thou payest no heed
  80,11,No indeed; it is a Reminder
  80,12,"and whoso wills, shall remember it"
  80,13,upon pages high-honoured
  80,14,"uplifted, purified"
  80,15,by the hands of scribes
  80,16,"noble, pious"
  80,17,Perish Man! How unthankful he is
  80,18,Of what did He create him
  80,19,"Of a sperm-drop He created him, and determined him"
  80,20,then the way eased for him
  80,21,"then makes him to die, and buries him"
  80,22,"then, when He wills, He raises him"
  80,23,No indeed! Man has not accomplished His bidding
  80,24,Let Man consider his nourishment
  80,25,We poured out the rains abundantly
  80,26,then We split the earth in fissures
  80,27,and therein made the grains to grow
  80,28,"and vines, and reeds"
  80,29,"and olives, and palms"
  80,30,and dense-tree'd gardens
  80,31,"and fruits, and pastures"
  80,32,an enjoyment for you and your flocks
  80,33,And when the Blast shall sound
  80,34,upon the day when a man shall flee from his brother
  80,35,"his mother, his father"
  80,36,"his consort, his sons"
  80,37,every man that day shall have business to suffice him
  80,38,Some faces on that day shall shine
  80,39,"laughing, joyous"
  80,40,some faces on that day shall be dusty
  80,41,o'erspread with darkness
  80,42,"those -- they are the unbelievers, the libertines"
  81,1,When the sun shall be darkened
  81,2,when the stars shall be thrown down
  81,3,when the mountains shall be set moving
  81,4,when the pregnant camels shall be neglected
  81,5,when the savage beasts shall be mustered
  81,6,when the seas shall be set boiling
  81,7,when the souls shall be coupled
  81,8,when the buried infant shall be asked
  81,9,for what sin she was slain
  81,10,when the scrolls shall be unrolled
  81,11,when heaven shall be stripped off
  81,12,when Hell shall be set blazing
  81,13,when Paradise shall be brought nigh
  81,14,then shall a soul know what it has produced
  81,15,No! I swear by the slinkers
  81,16,"the runners, the sinkers"
  81,17,by the night swarming
  81,18,by the dawn sighing
  81,19,truly this is the word of a noble Messenger
  81,20,"having power, with the Lord of the Throne secure"
  81,21,"obeyed, moreover trusty"
  81,22,Your companion is not possessed
  81,23,he truly saw him on the clear horizon
  81,24,he is not niggardly of the Unseen
  81,25,And it is not the word of an accursed Satan
  81,26,where then are you going
  81,27,It is naught but a Reminder unto all beings
  81,28,for whosoever of you who would go straight
  81,29,"but will you shall not, unless God wills, the Lord of all Being"
  82,1,When heaven is split open
  82,2,when the stars are scattered
  82,3,when the seas swarm over
  82,4,when the tombs are overthrown
  82,5,"then a soul shall know its works, the former and the latter"
  82,6,O Man! What deceived thee as to thy generous Lord
  82,7,who created thee and shaped thee and wrought thee in symmetry
  82,8,and composed thee after what form He would
  82,9,No indeed; but you cry lies to the Doom
  82,10,yet there are over you watchers
  82,11,"noble, writers"
  82,12,who know whatever you do
  82,13,Surely the pious shall be in bliss
  82,14,and the libertines shall be in a fiery furnace
  82,15,roasting therein on the Day of Doom
  82,16,nor shall they ever be absent from it
  82,17,And what shall teach thee what is the Day of Doom
  82,18,"Again, what shall teach thee what is the Day of Doom"
  82,19,A day when no soul shall possess aught to succour another soul; that day the Command shall belong unto God
  83,1,Woe to the stinters who
  83,2,"when they measure against the people, take full measure"
  83,3,"but, when they measure for them or weigh for them, do skimp"
  83,4,Do those not think that they shall be raised up
  83,5,unto a mighty day
  83,6,a day when mankind shall stand before the Lord of all Being
  83,7,No indeed; the Book of the libertines is in Sijjin
  83,8,and what shall teach thee what is Sijjin
  83,9,A book inscribed
  83,10,Woe that day unto those who cry it lies
  83,11,who cry lies to the Day of Doom
  83,12,and none cries lies to it but every guilty aggressor
  83,13,"When our signs are recited to him, he says, 'Fairy-tales of the ancients"
  83,14,No indeed; but that they were earning has rusted upon their hearts
  83,15,No indeed; but upon that day they shall be veiled from their Lord
  83,16,then they shall roast in Hell
  83,17,"Then it shall be said to them, 'This is that you cried lies to"
  83,18,No indeed; the book of the pious is in Illiyun
  83,19,and what shall teach thee what is Illiyun
  83,20,A book inscribed
  83,21,witnessed by those brought nigh
  83,22,Surely the pious shall be in bliss
  83,23,upon couches gazing
  83,24,thou knowest in their faces the radiancy of bliss
  83,25,as they are given to drink of a wine sealed
  83,26,whose seal is musk -- so after that let the strivers strive
  83,27,and whose mixture is Tasnim
  83,28,a fountain at which do drink those brought nigh
  83,29,"Behold, the sinners were laughing at the believers"
  83,30,when them passed them by winking at one another
  83,31,and when they returned to their people they returned blithely
  83,32,"and when they saw them they said, 'Lo, these men are astray"
  83,33,Yet they were not sent as watchers over them
  83,34,So today the believers are laughing at the unbelievers
  83,35,upon couches gazing
  83,36,Have the unbelievers been rewarded what they were doing
  84,1,When heaven is rent asunder
  84,2,"and gives ear to its Lord, and is fitly disposed"
  84,3,when earth is stretched out
  84,4,"and casts forth what is in it, and voids itself"
  84,5,"and gives ear to its Lord, and is fitly disposed"
  84,6,"O Man! Thou art labouring unto thy Lord laboriously, and thou shalt encounter Him"
  84,7,Then as for him who is given his book in his right hand
  84,8,he shall surely receive an easy reckoning
  84,9,and he will return to his family joyfully
  84,10,But as for him who is given his book behind his back
  84,11,he shall call for destruction
  84,12,and he shall roast at a Blaze
  84,13,He once lived among his family joyfully
  84,14,he surely thought he would never revert
  84,15,Yes indeed; his Lord had sight of him
  84,16,No! I swear by the twilight
  84,17,and the night and what it envelops
  84,18,and the moon when it is at the full
  84,19,you shall surely ride stage after stage
  84,20,"Then what ails them, that they believe not"
  84,21,and when the Koran is recited to them they do not bow
  84,22,"Nay, but the unbelievers are crying lies"
  84,23,and God knows very well what they are secreting
  84,24,So give them good tidings of a painful chastisement
  84,25,"except those that believe, and do righteous deeds -- theirs shall be a wage unfailing"
  85,1,By heaven of the constellations
  85,2,by the promised day
  85,3,by the witness and the witnessed
  85,4,slain were the Men of the Pit
  85,5,the fire abounding in fuel
  85,6,when they were seated over it
  85,7,and were themselves witnesses of what they did with the believers
  85,8,"They took revenge on them only because they believed in the All-mighty, the Al-laudable"
  85,9,"God to whom belongs the Kingdom of the heavens and the earth, and God is Witness over everything"
  85,10,"Those who persecute the believers, men and women, and then have not repented, there awaits them the chastisement of Gehenna, and there awaits them the chastisement of the burning"
  85,11,"Those who believe, and do righteous deeds, for them await gardens underneath which rivers flow; that is the great triumph"
  85,12,Surely thy Lord's assault is terrible
  85,13,"Surely it is He who originates, and brings again"
  85,14,"and He is the All-forgiving, the All-loving"
  85,15,"Lord of the Throne, the All-glorious"
  85,16,Performer of what He desires
  85,17,Hast thou received the story of the hosts
  85,18,Pharaoh and Thamood
  85,19,"Nay, but the unbelievers still cry lies"
  85,20,"and God is behind them, encompassing"
  85,21,"Nay, but it is a glorious Koran"
  85,22,in a guarded tablet
  86,1,By heaven and the night-star
  86,2,And what shall teach thee what is the night-star
  86,3,The piercing star
  86,4,Over every soul there is a watcher
  86,5,So let man consider of what he was created
  86,6,he was created of gushing water
  86,7,issuing between the loins and the breast-bones
  86,8,Surely He is able to bring him back
  86,9,upon the day when the secrets are tried
  86,10,"and he shall have no strength, no helper"
  86,11,By heaven of the returning rain
  86,12,by earth splitting with verdure
  86,13,surely it is a decisive word
  86,14,it is no merriment
  86,15,They are devising guile
  86,16,and I am devising guile
  86,17,So respite the unbelievers; delay with them awhile
  87,1,Magnify the Name of thy Lord the Most High
  87,2,who created and shaped
  87,3,who determined and guided
  87,4,who brought forth the pasturage
  87,5,then made it a blackening wrack
  87,6,"We shall make thee recite, to forget not"
  87,7,save what God wills; surely He knows what is spoken aloud and what is hidden
  87,8,We shall ease thee unto the Easing
  87,9,"Therefore remind, if the Reminder profits"
  87,10,and he who fears shall remember
  87,11,but the most wretched shall flout it
  87,12,even he who shall roast in the Great Fire
  87,13,"then he shall neither die therein, nor live"
  87,14,Prosperous is he who has cleansed himself
  87,15,"and mentions the Name of his Lord, and prays"
  87,16,"Nay, but you prefer the present life"
  87,17,"and the world to come is better, and more enduring"
  87,18,Surely this is in the ancient scrolls
  87,19,the scrolls of Abraham and Moses
  88,1,Hast thou received the story of the Enveloper
  88,2,Faces on that day humbled
  88,3,"labouring, toilworn"
  88,4,roasting at a scorching fire
  88,5,watered at a boiling fountain
  88,6,no food for them but cactus thorn
  88,7,"unfattening, unappeasing hunger"
  88,8,Faces on that day jocund
  88,9,with their striving well-pleased
  88,10,in a sublime Garden
  88,11,hearing there no babble
  88,12,therein a running fountain
  88,13,therein uplifted couches
  88,14,and goblets set forth
  88,15,and cushions arrayed
  88,16,and carpets outspread
  88,17,"What, do they not consider how the camel was created"
  88,18,how heaven was lifted up
  88,19,how the mountains were hoisted
  88,20,how the earth was outstretched
  88,21,Then remind them! Thou art only a reminder
  88,22,thou art not charged to oversee them
  88,23,"But he who turns his back, and disbelieves"
  88,24,God shall chastise him with the greatest chastisement
  88,25,"Truly, to Us is their return"
  88,26,then upon Us shall rest their reckoning
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,and ten nights
  89,3,by the even and the odd
  89,4,by the night when it journeys on
  89,5,Is there in that an oath for a mindful man
  89,6,Hast thou not seen how thy Lord did with Ad
  89,7,Iram of the pillars
  89,8,the like of which was never created in the land
  89,9,"and Thamood, who hollowed the rocks in the valley"
  89,10,"and Pharaoh, he of the tent-pegs"
  89,11,who all were insolent in the land
  89,12,and worked much corruption therein
  89,13,Thy Lord unloosed on them a scourge of chastisement
  89,14,surely thy Lord is ever on the watch
  89,15,"As for man, whenever his Lord tries him, and honours him, and blesses him, then he says, 'My Lord has honoured me"
  89,16,"But when he tries him and stints for him his provision, then he says, 'My Lord has despised me"
  89,17,No indeed; but you honour not the orphan
  89,18,and you urge not the feeding of the needy
  89,19,and you devour the inheritance greedily
  89,20,and you love wealth with an ardent love
  89,21,No indeed! When the earth is ground to powder
  89,22,"and thy Lord comes, and the angels rank on rank"
  89,23,"and Gehenna is brought out, upon that day man will remember; and how shall the Reminder be for him"
  89,24,"He shall say, 'O would that I had forwarded for my life"
  89,25,Upon that day none shall chastise as He chastises
  89,26,none shall bind as He binds
  89,27,O soul at peace
  89,28,"return unto thy Lord, well-pleased, well-pleasing"
  89,29,Enter thou among My servants
  89,30,Enter thou My Paradise
  90,1,No! I swear by this land
  90,2,and thou art a lodger in this land
  90,3,"by the begetter, and that he begot"
  90,4,"indeed, We created man in trouble"
  90,5,"What, does he think none has power over him"
  90,6,"saying, 'I have consumed wealth abundant"
  90,7,"What, does he think none has seen him"
  90,8,Have We not appointed to him two eyes
  90,9,"and a tongue, and two lips"
  90,10,and guided him on the two highways
  90,11,Yet he has not assaulted the steep
  90,12,and what shall teach thee what is the steep
  90,13,The freeing of a slave
  90,14,or giving food upon a day of hunger
  90,15,to an orphan near of kin
  90,16,or a needy man in misery
  90,17,"then that he become of those who believe and counsel each other to be steadfast, and counsel each other to be merciful"
  90,18,Those are the Companions of the Right Hand
  90,19,"And those who disbelieve in Our signs, they are the Companions of the Left Hand"
  90,20,over them is a Fire covered down
  91,1,By the sun and his morning brightness
  91,2,and by the moon when she follows him
  91,3,and by the day when it displays him
  91,4,and by the night when it enshrouds him
  91,5,By the heaven and That which built it
  91,6,and by the earth and That which extended it
  91,7,"By the soul, and That which shaped it"
  91,8,and inspired it to lewdness and godfearing
  91,9,Prosperous is he who purifies it
  91,10,and failed has he who seduces it
  91,11,Thamood cried lies in their insolence
  91,12,when the most wretched of them uprose
  91,13,"then the Messenger of God said to them, 'The She-camel of God; let her drink"
  91,14,"But they cried him lies, and hamstrung her, so their Lord crushed them for their sin, and leveled them"
  91,15,and He fears not the issue thereof
  92,1,By the night enshrouding
  92,2,and the day in splendour
  92,3,and That which created the male and the female
  92,4,surely your striving is to diverse ends
  92,5,As for him who gives and is godfearing
  92,6,and confirms the reward most fair
  92,7,We shall surely ease him to the Easing
  92,8,"But as for him who is a miser, and self-sufficient"
  92,9,and cries lies to the reward most fair
  92,10,We shall surely ease him to the Hardship
  92,11,his wealth shall not avail him when he perishes
  92,12,Surely upon Us rests the guidance
  92,13,and to Us belong the Last and the First
  92,14,Now I have warned you of a Fire that flames
  92,15,whereat none but the most wretched shall be roasted
  92,16,"even he who cried lies, and turned away"
  92,17,and from which the most godfearing shall be removed
  92,18,even he who gives his wealth. to purify himself
  92,19,and confers no favour on any man for recompense
  92,20,only seeking the Face of his Lord the Most High
  92,21,and he shall surely be satisfied
  93,1,By the white forenoon
  93,2,and the brooding night
  93,3,Thy Lord has neither forsaken thee nor hates thee
  93,4,and the Last shall be better for thee than the First
  93,5,"Thy Lord shall give thee, and thou shalt be satisfied"
  93,6,"Did He not find thee an orphan, and shelter thee"
  93,7,"Did He not find thee erring, and guide thee"
  93,8,"Did He not find thee needy, and suffice thee"
  93,9,"As for the orphan, do not oppress him"
  93,10,"and as for the beggar, scold him not"
  93,11,"and as for thy Lord's blessing, declare it"
  94,1,Did We not expand thy breast for thee
  94,2,and lift from thee thy burden
  94,3,the burden that weighed down thy back
  94,4,Did We not exalt thy fame
  94,5,So truly with hardship comes ease
  94,6,truly with hardship comes ease
  94,7,"So when thou art empty, labour"
  94,8,and let thy Lord be thy Quest
  95,1,By the fig and the olive
  95,2,and the Mount Sinai
  95,3,and this land secure
  95,4,We indeed created Man in the fairest stature
  95,5,then We restored him the lowest of the low
  95,6,"save those who believe, and do righteous deeds; they shall have a wage unfailing"
  95,7,What then shall cry thee lies as to the Doom
  95,8,Is not God the justest of judges
  96,1,"Recite: In the Name of thy Lord who created"
  96,2,created Man of a blood-clot
  96,3,"Recite: And thy Lord is the Most Generous"
  96,4,who taught by the Pen
  96,5,taught Man that he knew not
  96,6,No indeed; surely Man waxes insolent
  96,7,for he thinks himself self-sufficient
  96,8,Surely unto thy Lord is the Returning
  96,9,What thinkest thou? He who forbids
  96,10,a servant when he prays
  96,11,What thinkest thou? If he were upon guidance
  96,12,or bade to godfearing
  96,13,"What thinkest thou? If he cries lies, and turns away"
  96,14,Did he not know that God sees
  96,15,"No indeed; surely, if he gives not over, We shall seize him by the forelock"
  96,16,"a lying, sinful forelock"
  96,17,So let him call on his concourse
  96,18,We shall call on the guards of Hell
  96,19,"No indeed; do thou not obey him, and bow thyself, and draw nigh"
  97,1,"Behold, We sent it down on the Night of Power"
  97,2,And what shall teach thee what is the Night of Power
  97,3,The Night of Power is better than a thousand months
  97,4,"in it the angels and the Spirit descend, by the leave of their Lord, upon every command"
  97,5,"Peace it is, till the rising of dawn"
  98,1,The unbelievers of the People of the Book and the idolaters would never leave off; till the Clear Sign came to them
  98,2,"a Messenger from God, reciting pages purified"
  98,3,therein true Books
  98,4,"And they scattered not, those that were given the Book, excepting after the Clear Sign came to them"
  98,5,"They were commanded only to serve God, making the religion His sincerely, men of pure faith, and to perform the prayer, and pay the alms -- that is the religion of the True"
  98,6,"The unbelievers of the People of the Book and the idolaters shall be in the Fire of Gehenna, therein dwelling forever; those are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,"But those who believe, and do righteous deeds, those are the best of creatures"
  98,8,"their recompense is with their Lord-Gardens of Eden, underneath which rivers flow, therein dwelling for ever and ever. God is well-pleased with them, and they are well-pleased with Him; that is for him who fears his Lord"
  99,1,When earth is shaken with a mighty shaking
  99,2,and earth brings forth her burdens
  99,3,"and Man says., 'What ails her"
  99,4,upon that day she shall tell her tidings
  99,5,for that her Lord has inspired her
  99,6,Upon that day men shall issue in scatterings to see their works
  99,7,and whoso has done an atom's weight of good shall see it
  99,8,and whoso has done an atom's weight of evil shall see it
  100,1,By the snorting chargers
  100,2,by the strikers of fire
  100,3,by the dawn-raiders
  100,4,blazing a trail of dust
  100,5,cleaving there with a host
  100,6,Surely Man is ungrateful to his Lord
  100,7,and surely he is a witness against that
  100,8,Surely he is passionate in his love for good things
  100,9,Knows he not that when that which is in the tombs is over-thrown
  100,10,and that which is in the breasts is brought out
  100,11,surely on that day their Lord shall be aware of them
  101,1,The Clatterer
  101,2,What is the Clatterer
  101,3,And what shall teach thee what is the Clatterer
  101,4,The day that men shall be like scattered moths
  101,5,and the mountains shall be like plucked wool-tufts
  101,6,Then he whose deeds weigh heavy in the Balance
  101,7,shall inherit a pleasing life
  101,8,but he whose deeds weigh light in the Balance
  101,9,shall plunge in the womb of the Pit
  101,10,And what shall teach thee what is the Pit
  101,11,A blazing Fire
  102,1,Gross rivalry diverts you
  102,2,even till you visit the tombs
  102,3,No indeed; but soon you shall know
  102,4,"Again, no indeed; but soon you shall know"
  102,5,No indeed; did you know with the knowledge of certainty
  102,6,you shall surely see Hell
  102,7,"Again, you shall surely see it with the eye of certainty"
  102,8,then you shall be questioned that day concerning true bliss
  103,1,By the afternoon
  103,2,Surely Man is in the way of loss
  103,3,"save those who believe, and do righteous deeds, and counsel each other unto the truth, and counsel each other to be steadfast"
  104,1,"Woe unto every backbiter, slanderer"
  104,2,who has gathered riches and counted them over
  104,3,thinking his riches have made him immortal
  104,4,No indeed; he shall be thrust into the Crusher
  104,5,and what shall teach thee what is the Crusher
  104,6,The Fire of God kindled
  104,7,roaring over the hearts
  104,8,covered down upon them
  104,9,in columns outstretched
  105,1,Hast thou not seen how thy Lord did with the Men of the Elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their guile to go astray
  105,3,And He loosed upon them birds in flights
  105,4,hurling against them stones of baked clay
  105,5,and He made them like green blades devoured
  106,1,For the composing of Koraish
  106,2,their composing for the winter and summer caravan
  106,3,So let them serve the Lord of this House
  106,4,who has fed them against hunger and secured them from fear
  107,1,Hast thou seen him who cries lies to the Doom
  107,2,That is he who repulses the orphan
  107,3,and urges not the feeding of the needy
  107,4,So woe to those that pray
  107,5,and are heedless of their prayers
  107,6,to those who make display
  107,7,and refuse charity
  108,1,Surely We have given thee abundance
  108,2,so pray unto thy Lord and sacrifice
  108,3,"Surely he that hates thee, he is the one cut off"
  109,1,"Say: 'O unbelievers"
  109,2,I serve not what you serve
  109,3,and you are not serving what I serve
  109,4,nor am I serving what you have served
  109,5,neither are you serving what I serve
  109,6,"To you your religion, and to me my religion"
  110,1,"When comes the help of God, and victory"
  110,2,and thou seest men entering God's religion in throngs
  110,3,"then proclaim the praise of thy Lord, and seek His forgiveness; for He turns again unto men"
  111,1,"Perish the hands of Abu Lahab, and perish he"
  111,2,"His wealth avails him not, neither what he has earned"
  111,3,he shall roast at a flaming fire
  111,4,"and his wife, the carrier of the firewood"
  111,5,upon her neck a rope of palm-fibre
  112,1,"Say: 'He is God, One"
  112,2,"God, the Everlasting Refuge"
  112,3,"who has not begotten, and has not been begotten"
  112,4,and equal to Him is not any one
  113,1,"Say: 'I take refuge with the Lord of the Daybreak"
  113,2,from the evil of what He has created
  113,3,from the evil of darkness when it gathers
  113,4,from the evil of the women who blow on knots
  113,5,from the evil of an envier when he envies
  114,1,"Say: 'I take refuge with the Lord of men"
  114,2,the King of men
  114,3,the God of men
  114,4,from the evil of the slinking whisperer
  114,5,who whispers in the breasts of men
  114,6,of jinn and men